<!-- ABOUT SECTION -->
<section class="about-section">
    <h2>About PharmaGuard</h2>
    <p>
        PharmaGuard is an advanced pharmacogenomic intelligence platform
        designed to bridge the gap between genomics and clinical decision-making.
        By combining variant-level genetic insights with AI-driven prediction models,
        we help healthcare professionals prescribe safer, more effective medications.
    </p>

    <p>
        Adverse Drug Reactions (ADRs) are among the leading causes of preventable
        hospitalizations worldwide. Many of these reactions occur due to genetic
        differences in drug metabolism. PharmaGuard analyzes clinically significant
        pharmacogenes and transforms raw genomic data into actionable insights.
    </p>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section class="process-section">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>

    <div class="process-step">
        <h3>1. Upload Genetic Data</h3>
        <p>
            Users upload validated VCF (Variant Call Format) files containing
            genomic variant information.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
        <h3>2. Variant Interpretation</h3>
        <p>
            The system detects gene variants in CYP2D6, CYP2C19, CYP2C9,
            SLCO1B1, TPMT, and DPYD and determines metabolizer status.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
        <h3>3. AI Risk Prediction</h3>
        <p>
            Our hybrid rule-based and AI model evaluates potential toxicity,
            ineffectiveness, or dosage adjustments for selected medications.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="process-step">
        <h3>4. Explainable Clinical Output</h3>
        <p>
            A detailed explanation is generated, aligned with CPIC guidelines,
            ensuring transparency and interpretability for clinicians.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

